<br>
The cause of all suffering, according to the Buddha, is hopes and expectations - to achieve nirvana (which literally means cessation) - one is to give up all hopes and expectations. Life is misery. When you except that, it won't make you miserable anymore. <br>
<br>
Basically (and in the extreme) if you don't care if you survive, and have learned to accept hunger and cold as sensations rather than needs, you will be happy. Well... happy isn't the right word; that implies ego. Maybe &quot;you will not be unhappy&quot; is a better way of putting it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
